The paper deals with the computational complexity of a self-assembly problem, which involves the manipulation of patterns of tiles. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG) in the analysis of the problem. Finally, the paper deals with the self-assembly of physical structures, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SC).
